				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There wasn't any existing test ROM to see what kind of MMC3 chip any given board has, so here's one. It will show you which of the wiki's &quot;IRQ tick happens at 260,268,276... or 315&quot; pixel values is correct for your chip.<br /><br />The offset is 195 pixels, so if you measure the effect starting at 169 pixels, 169 - 195 + 341 = 315, that chip would be the 315 type.<br /><br />Mednafen is exactly correct, fceux seems to be off by 8 pixels.</div>

					
